{#- ### Top Mitigations — single table with per-component group-header rows.

    Layout (2026-05-28 — item 2 user request: ONE table grouped by
    component, not per-component sub-tables):

      | # | Priority | Mitigation | Addresses | Effort |
      |---|---|---|---|---|
      | **↳ <Component Name> (<c-id>) — N item(s)** |||||
      | 1 | P1 | ... |
      | 2 | P1 | ... |
      | **↳ <Next Component> — M item(s)** |||||
      | 3 | P1 | ... |

    Group-header rows use blank trailing cells; common Markdown renderers
    (GFM, Pandoc, weasyprint) render them as a single bold line spanning
    the table visually. The previous template's per-component sub-tables
    rendered as fragmented mini-tables that broke the at-a-glance scan.

    Inputs:
      groups    : list of { header, divider_label, include_affects_column, mitigations[] }
                  - header:        optional `####` sub-header (legacy); usually None
                  - divider_label: paragraph divider text per group ("↳ Component …")
                  - mitigations[]: data rows with continuous global numbering
                                   { number, id, title, primary_component_id,
                                     addresses[{ref,label}], effort, priority }
                                   Pre-sorted: P1 → P2, severity, effort, ID.
      intro     : top-of-section paragraph string (mentions §9 register)
      footer    : optional italic footer line under the table (may be None)
-#}
### Top Mitigations

{{ intro }}

| # | Priority | Mitigation | Addresses | Effort |
|---|---|---|---|---|
{%- for g in groups %}
{#- The composer's `divider_label` already ships with a leading "↳ "
    glyph (see `_render_mitigations` in compose_threat_model.py); don't
    re-prepend one here or rows render as `↳ ↳ Component …`.
    Strip a leading "↳ " if present so legacy callers without it still
    render with the glyph. -#}
{%- if g.divider_label %}
{%- set _lbl = g.divider_label | trim %}
{%- if _lbl.startswith("↳ ") %}
| **{{ _lbl }}** | | | | |
{%- else %}
| **↳ {{ _lbl }}** | | | | |
{%- endif %}
{%- endif %}
{%- for m in g.mitigations %}
| **{{ m.number }}** | **{{ m.priority }}** | [{{ m.id }}](#{{ m.id | lower }}) — {{ m.title }} | {% for a in m.addresses %}[{{ a.ref | replace('T-', 'F-') }}](#{{ (a.ref | replace('T-', 'F-')) | lower }}){% if a.label %} — {{ a.label }}{% endif %}{% if not loop.last %}<br/>{% endif %}{% endfor %} | {{ m.effort }} |
{%- endfor %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- if footer %}

{{ footer }}
{% endif %}
